org.assertj.guava.api.MultimapAssert

    Package Description
    org.assertj.guava.api  

    • Uses of MultimapAssert in org.assertj.guava.api

      Methods in org.assertj.guava.api that return MultimapAssert 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static <K,V> MultimapAssert<K,V> Assertions.assertThat(com.google.common.collect.Multimap<K,V> actual) 
      MultimapAssert<K,V> MultimapAssert.contains(org.assertj.core.data.MapEntry<K,V>... entries)
      Verifies that the actual Multimap contains the given entries.
      MultimapAssert<K,V> MultimapAssert.containsAllEntriesOf(com.google.common.collect.Multimap<? extends K,? extends V> other)
      Verifies that the actual Multimap contains all entries of the given one (it might contain more entries).
      MultimapAssert<K,V> MultimapAssert.containsKeys(K... keys)
      Verifies that the actual Multimap contains the given keys.
      MultimapAssert<K,V> MultimapAssert.containsValues(V... values)
      Verifies that the actual Multimap contains the given values for any key.
      MultimapAssert<K,V> MultimapAssert.hasSameEntriesAs(com.google.common.collect.Multimap<? extends K,? extends V> other)
      Verifies that the actual Multimap has the same entries as the given one.
      It allows to compare two multimaps having the same content but who are not equal because being of different types like SetMultimap and ListMultimap.
      MultimapAssert<K,V> MultimapAssert.hasSize(int expectedSize)
      Verifies that the number of values in the actual Multimap is equal to the given one.
